N

Node - Class in object
Node objects consist of a label as well as co-ordinates and are used as part of connection objects to both get input and output of graphs and/or trees.
Node(String, Point) - Constructor for class object.Node
Default constructor, used to create a new node when taking in a label and co-ordinates.
Node(String[]) - Constructor for class object.Node
Constructor used when opening a saved file, it will get a line of text from the nodes.txt and pass it as a string array with each token of the line in a separate place in the format Label x y
NODE_LABEL - Variable in class object.Node
This is the name the user has given to the node, which must be unique as methods are called to get nodes based on their label.
nodeDiameter - Static variable in class graphics.ProblemGraphGraphicsComponent
The diameter of the node.
nodeDiameter - Static variable in class graphics.SolutionGraphGraphicsComponent
The diameter of the node.
nodeList - Static variable in class object.Node
This array list is a dynamic data structure that will hold all nodes that are in the solution and problem.
nodeMode - Variable in class graphics.CustomActionListener
Booleans to determine action to take on mouse events
nodeMode - Variable in class graphics.ProblemGraphPanel
These JButtons are the buttons at the top of the JPanel and all have action commands equal to their name
nodes - Variable in class graphics.ProblemGraphGraphicsComponent
The ArrayList of nodes to draw
nodes - Variable in class graphics.SolutionGraphGraphicsComponent
The ArrayList of nodes to draw
nodes - Variable in class object.Connection
A node array of size two that contains both the nodes of the connection.
nodeSearch(Point) - Method in class graphics.CustomActionListener
Find a node based on the point on screen, used to move, check for nodes and delete nodes.
normLabel() - Method in class object.Node
Normalises the label, returning it as a UPPERCASE string
